caption: Figure 6: SHD vs number of interventional samples for random complete graphs. We generate 50 random DAGs and plot the average SHD and standard deviation. scm-v0 and neurips-rff are pretrained models in the paper.
description: This figure compares the performance of the proposed algorithm against two other Bayesian causal discovery methods (scm-v0 and neurips-rff) on random complete graphs.  The Structural Hamming Distance (SHD), a measure of the difference between learned and true causal graphs, is plotted against the number of interventional samples. The average SHD and standard deviation across 50 random DAGs are shown.
